A. Project Overview
Problem Statement: Development teams waste time on repetitive DevOps tasks, struggle with inconsistent environments, and face deployment errors due to manual processes.

Real-World Use Case: A tech company with multiple microservices needs standardized CI/CD pipelines, automated infrastructure provisioning, and consistent deployment processes across development, staging, and production environments.

Target Users: DevOps engineers, SREs, platform engineers, development teams, and startups needing scalable DevOps automation.

B. Tech Stack
Core Language: Python 3.9+

Infrastructure as Code: Terraform, CloudFormation templates

CI/CD: Custom pipeline runner, GitHub Actions integration

Containerization: Docker, Docker Compose, Kubernetes manifests

Configuration Management: Ansible, Python config libraries

Cloud Providers: AWS, Azure, GCP (multi-cloud support)

Monitoring: Prometheus exporters, Grafana dashboards

Tools: Click CLI, Jinja2 templating, SSH/paramiko, GitPython
